A couple and their three children were found dead on Saturday morning inside their rented single room house in Githurai 45, Kiambu County.
Police suspect the five -  a father, mother and their three children - died from carbon monoxide poisoning.
Ruiru divisional police commander (OCPD) Phineas Lingera told the Nation that the man sold boiled maize in the area and may have lit a jiko to prepare the commodity for the next day.



